track_notes:
From Cwmorthin Road parking spot - or take the steam train to Tanygrisiau. Cross river over footbridge to join Stwlan dam access road. My track leaves just short of the dam, to climb beside disused tramway incline. But access across the dam looked clear.

Rise to Bwlch Stwlan. Turn right up ridge to Craigysgafn - some exposure here, but grit your teeth and it will soon be over. Continue the climb to Moelwyn Mawr summit.

See also my route to Allt Fawr GW/NW-025, which could be picked up from Rhosydd slate quarry for another easy approach.

From car park past the end of Cwmorthin Road head north and cross Afon Cwmorthin. This would be at SH 68154570 except the path is closed due to scouring out below the bridge; so you have to go to SH 67914600, almost at Llyn Cwmorthin. Back-track south and follow track zig-zagging up the slate waste to the disused Wrysgan Quarry. After exploring the remains, especially the exit tramway tunnel, climb the incline to the higher level.

Continue along path below Moel-yr-hydd. Pass to other side of electric fence at gate and follow fence line to the south-east shoulder of Moelwyn Mawr. Pass through another gate and up steep grassy slope to summit.

From car park past end of Cwmorthin Road, head north. Pass remains of Cwmorthin Quarry to keep left of Llyn Cwmorthin. Pass ruins of Capel Rhosydd at SH 67284641. Follow Bwlch Cwmorthin track to New Rhosydd Quarry. Climb incline to higher tips. Head cross stile at SH 66404582 (or another further SSE) and cut across softer ground to south. Short of original Rhosydd Quarry site tracks turns up the north-east shoulder of Moelwyn Mawr.

Total time (including ops): 5hr 25m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T2. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Allt Fawr and Moelwyn Mawr Circuit from Tan y grisiau. Dec 2020.
